## Definition

An $R$-[[associative algebra|algebra]] $A$ is _Ã©tale_ if the definition [[homomorphism]] $R \to A$ is, dually, an [[Ã©tale morphism of schemes]].

A more elementary definition for algebras over a discrete field exists in constructive algebra.

